results.name: Number of composite divisors of n.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(n) = tau(n)-omega(n)-1, where tau=A000005 and omega=A001221. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 13 2003
G.f.: -x/(1 - x) + Sum_{k>=1} (x^k - x^prime(k))/((1 - x^k)*(1 - x^prime(k))). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Mar 21 2017
example: a[20] = 3 because the composite divisors of 20 are 4, 10, 20.
mathematica: Table[Count[Divisors[n],_?CompositeQ],{n,120}] (* Requires Mathematica version 10 or later *) (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Jul 09 2018 *)
